  "prompt": "Was Charles Lee related to Robert E. Lee?",
  "response": "Charles Lee and Robert E. Lee were not closely related, but they shared a distant familial connection. Charles Lee was a general during the American Revolutionary War, while Robert E. Lee was a Confederate general during the American Civil War. Both men belonged to prominent Virginia families, and their families intermarried over the generations.\n\nCharles Lee's brother, Richard Henry Lee, was a signer of the Declaration of Independence. Richard Henry Lee's great-granddaughter, Mary Anna Randolph Custis, married Robert E. Lee, making Charles Lee and Robert E. Lee very distant relatives by marriage. The connection is quite removed, as it spans several generations and involves multiple familial lines.",
